adjectives.description: unparsonic (comparative more unparsonic, superlative most unparsonic)

entries.meaning: Not like a parson; unbecoming of a parson.
examples: He enunciated the grace in slightly unparsonic tones, which implied that he was not only Rector of Rotherden, but also a full member of the M.C.C. and first cousin once removed to Lord Chatwynd.
